      {
        "position": 1,
        "title": "Really good price for the quality",
        "text": "My 100 lb Aussie/Pyrenees mix LOVES this bed. Bought the XL and it's plenty big for him to stretch out on his side. The raised sides make a nice bolster for his head and the memory foam is really thick and firm in the mattress. The fuzzy material is really a nice quality--my cats steal naps in it when Dexter isn't using it! Good price and good quality.",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "November 17, 2025",
        "author": "Alicia Melvin",
        "author_link": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFVL76UO5DIP2XRT2S3V2FQKDBYQ",
        "author_image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/amazon-avatars-global/default.png",
        "helpful_votes": "One person found this helpful",
        "product": {
          "size": "Orthopedic 44\"L x 32\"W x 8\"TH",
          "color": "Camel"
        }
      },
      {
        "position": 2,
        "title": "Wonderful dog bed",
        "text": "Wonderful dog bed. Super soft exterior. The bed itself is sturdy and comfortable for my 70 lb Pittie. This bed fits well in his crate.",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "December 7, 2025",
        "author": "Jennifer bishop",
        "author_link": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEPYLYCUWPRVQRJ5K4FMITHWRLRA",
        "author_image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/amazon-avatars-global/default.png"
      },
      {
        "position": 3,
        "title": "Doggo loves",
        "text": "I bought this dog bed as my dog's Christmas gift after falling into a bit of a doggie bed rabbit hole for cuddle beds. Most of them are round donut shaped beds. They all have the characteristic of being shaggy or furry rather than smooth. They are supposed to make your doggo feel like they're being hugged or sleeping in a dog pile. Anyway, my little man is aging now at 13 (maybe. He was a rescue we adopted in 2013, so the age is a guess.) and I was reading reviews that these donut cuddle beds were too thin or sagged in the middle where the dog sleeps. Also we just don't have the space for a round style bed, so into the rabbit hole searching for a rectangle orthopedic version. This is the one I found, and for the smallest size, it was also the most expensive version. I see now that it's selling for $23 in the size I bought, but looking back at my invoice, I paid almost $31 for the smallest size. Now, my dog doesn't care for anything new, like a new bed, so it took a bit of us picking him up and putting him on there, or dropping his favorite fleece blanket over top and then putting him on there to get him used to the idea that this bed is his. Finally as of a month or two or so ago, he now heading there and snoozing the hard snoozes of an older dog. When my husband works from home, the bed is typically besides his desk, and he'll tell me the dog was out sound asleep in it most of the day. Sometimes when I come home from work on the days my husband's at the office, he'll be sleeping on it instead of inside his crate, which always surprises me because he has chosen for years to sleep the day away in his crate when he's home alone.This bed is HEAVY! Easily the heaviest bed in this size we've ever bought. It's also very generous in size. I wasn't sure if the 26x18 would be quite big enough, but there's plenty of room to spare. My dog is a 13lb Toy Fox Terrier, so he's bigger than a Mini Pin or Chihuahua, but smaller than a Jack Russell. I think any breed like that in size would fit just fine in this size bed. The outside does unzip at the base and can be washed. I washed it in the gentle cycle and dried it in that cycle as well. Now that the price has dropped dramatically from when I bought it, don't hesitate to gift one to your dog. It's a heavy duty, well made product that should last for several years.",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "March 12, 2025",
        "author": "C. Floyd",
        "author_link": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEWQK5OVLEQDZX7QXSPBQGUGLJRA",
        "author_image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/amazon-avatars-global/default.png",
        "images": [
          "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/710J-41Y6gL._SY88.jpg"
        ],
        "helpful_votes": "10 people found this helpful"
      },
      {
        "position": 4,
        "title": "Dog approved!",
        "text": "Got this 38 inch for our border collie (38lbs). Item came well packaged. Though compressed it’s easy to set up. Feels super soft and comfy and the foam and structure provides great support! See how thick it is in the photo. The fabric is slightly shiny and glittery, designed in detail. No odor. Love the removable cover which makes cleaning it much easier. Definitely recommend.",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "August 3, 2025",
        "author": "MyLittleMaxy",
        "author_link": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEDSJJXUCD5YGONZEZP6EDIYN6MA",
        "author_image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/S/amazon-avatars-global/6cf47d23-b582-433e-a835-8e8f588be23c._CR0%2C0%2C500%2C500_SX460_.jpg",
        "images": [
